1
00:01:17,768 --> 00:01:20,168
[Man Screaming]

2
00:01:21,512 --> 00:01:23,720
[Screaming Continues]

3
00:01:25,448 --> 00:01:27,816
[Shrieking]

4
00:01:31,368 --> 00:01:34,056
Hey, why I always gotta get
the broken ones?

5
00:01:34,152 --> 00:01:37,224
- Try the trigger.
- [Metal Clatters]

6
00:01:37,320 --> 00:01:40,200
[Woman]
Father, I'm fighting this time.

7
00:01:40,296 --> 00:01:43,272
- Father!
- Go back in your room, Kyra.

8
00:01:43,368 --> 00:01:46,056
Get back in your room!

9
00:01:46,152 --> 00:01:48,936
Go inside, please.

10
00:01:53,256 --> 00:01:55,464
[ Whimpering ]

11
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:57,960
[Man Screaming]

12
00:01:59,272 --> 00:02:01,288
[Screaming Continues]

13
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:03,880
Aaah!
[ Grunting ]

14
00:02:06,184 --> 00:02:08,392
[Growling]

15
00:02:21,832 --> 00:02:23,656
[ Growls ]

16
00:02:23,752 --> 00:02:25,576
I can't see it.

17
00:02:28,456 --> 00:02:30,280
Fight me, butcher!

18
00:02:30,376 --> 00:02:33,032
[ Low Voice ]
Not you.

19
00:02:34,952 --> 00:02:37,160
[ Growling ]

20
00:02:41,864 --> 00:02:46,760
[Horn Blowing]

21
00:02:50,696 --> 00:02:53,192
[Hissing Sound]

22
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:02,472
[Panting]

23
00:03:02,568 --> 00:03:06,024
[Whimpering]

24
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:08,712
Aaah!

25
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:16,968
No more!

26
00:03:17,064 --> 00:03:20,136
[Man]
Bring her to the scaffold.

27
00:03:20,232 --> 00:03:22,056
Kill her!

28
00:03:22,728 --> 00:03:24,744
Someone help!

29
00:03:26,184 --> 00:03:28,008
[ Woman Protesting ]

30
00:03:29,928 --> 00:03:31,752
No!

31
00:03:34,408 --> 00:03:36,904
No!

32
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:41,032
Help me!

33
00:03:41,128 --> 00:03:42,952
[Horse Whinnies]

34
00:03:43,048 --> 00:03:45,064
No!

35
00:03:49,384 --> 00:03:51,880
[ Grunting ]

36
00:03:54,088 --> 00:03:56,296
[Man]
Quickly now. Somebody help!

37
00:03:56,392 --> 00:03:58,600
[Man]
You must die.

38
00:04:01,672 --> 00:04:03,880
Please stop!

39
00:04:17,192 --> 00:04:20,072
- [Man]Kill her!
- [ Gasping ]

40
00:04:23,432 --> 00:04:25,640
Maker of all
that is pure and good,

41
00:04:25,736 --> 00:04:30,152
we release this girl
from the evil that possesses her.

42
00:04:30,248 --> 00:04:32,744
- [ Chanting ] Kill the beast!
- You don't understand.

43
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:35,720
Kill the beast!
Kill the beast!

44
00:04:35,816 --> 00:04:38,760
Kill the beast!
Kill the beast!
Kill the beast!

45
00:04:38,952 --> 00:04:40,872
Kill the beast!
Kill the beast!

46
00:04:40,968 --> 00:04:43,080
Kill the beast!
Kill the beast!

47
00:04:43,176 --> 00:04:45,096
Kill the beast!
Kill the beast!

48
00:04:45,192 --> 00:04:47,304
- [Chanting Continues]
- [Horse Whinnies]

49
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:49,704
[ Chanting Dies Down ]

50
00:04:51,624 --> 00:04:55,080
[ Whinnying ]

51
00:05:01,224 --> 00:05:03,048
Cut her loose.

52
00:05:03,144 --> 00:05:05,544
She's from the outpost.

53
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:08,232
The place is infested
with evil.

54
00:05:08,328 --> 00:05:10,408
No one gets away
from there and lives.

55
00:05:13,096 --> 00:05:15,496
I said cut her loose.

56
00:05:16,744 --> 00:05:20,392
This conversation is over.
Now move on.

57
00:05:24,712 --> 00:05:26,728
[ Gasping ]

58
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:31,816
No!

59
00:05:31,912 --> 00:05:35,080
- [ Metal Creaks ]
- [ Gasps ]

60
00:05:35,176 --> 00:05:37,384
- Uhh!
- [Man]Come on!

61
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:39,592
- Let's get him!
- [ Shouting ]

62
00:06:06,728 --> 00:06:09,800
[All Shouting]

63
00:06:14,952 --> 00:06:16,776
[ Whinnies ]

64
00:06:16,968 --> 00:06:19,752
- Go.
- Hyah!

65
00:06:21,576 --> 00:06:23,400
Hyah!

66
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:41,064
Yaaah!

67
00:06:59,848 --> 00:07:01,288
Haaah!

68
00:07:03,112 --> 00:07:05,320
[ Grunts ]

69
00:07:22,184 --> 00:07:24,296
Aaah!

70
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:28,328
Aaaah!

71
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:41,768
[ Screaming ]

72
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:47,912
[Roaring]

73
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:55,464
[ Woman ]
No! No!

74
00:07:57,960 --> 00:07:59,880
Come on. Come on!
Haah!

75
00:08:08,904 --> 00:08:11,976
Enough. Enough!

76
00:08:12,072 --> 00:08:14,280
Yaah!

77
00:08:14,376 --> 00:08:16,872
-Just kidding.
- [ Sighs ]

78
00:08:18,792 --> 00:08:20,904
Take her and go.

79
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:24,328
Thank you, but I'm not
going that way.

80
00:08:31,048 --> 00:08:32,872
You're a dead man already.

81
00:08:32,968 --> 00:08:35,368
Let's go.

82
00:08:36,712 --> 00:08:38,920
[ Woman ]
So many are dead.

83
00:08:39,016 --> 00:08:41,224
I don't want to die.

84
00:08:45,928 --> 00:08:48,040
It comes and kills.

85
00:08:48,136 --> 00:08:50,920
It's killing everybody.
It's gonna kill you.

86
00:08:51,016 --> 00:08:52,840
Why did you run?

87
00:08:52,936 --> 00:08:55,400
[ Gasping ]
It's there.

88
00:08:55,496 --> 00:08:58,856
- It's in there.
- "It"? What is "it"?

89
00:08:58,952 --> 00:09:01,544
Every night.
It comes out every night.

90
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:04,712
Every night,
it's killing everyone.

91
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:14,504
- What's up?
- It's Pendra. She's alive.

92
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:16,424
Yeah,
but who is that with her?

93
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:19,208
And how the hell
did they get through?

94
00:09:19,304 --> 00:09:23,240
If they let him and her through,
well, may be it's over.

95
00:09:28,968 --> 00:09:31,464
[ Gasps ]

96
00:09:31,656 --> 00:09:34,056
Oh, no.

97
00:09:35,496 --> 00:09:37,608
How many people
left inside?

98
00:09:40,872 --> 00:09:42,888
- How many--
- [Woman Screams]

99
00:09:48,072 --> 00:09:49,896
[ Whimpering ]
No!

100
00:09:49,992 --> 00:09:53,544
[Men Cheering]

101
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:56,232
Yah!

102
00:09:56,328 --> 00:10:00,136
- Well, there's your answer, kid.
- She should've stayed.

103
00:10:00,328 --> 00:10:02,824
At least for her it's over.

104
00:10:04,456 --> 00:10:06,760
[Horse Whinnying
In Distance]

105
00:10:06,952 --> 00:10:10,696
Who are you
And what do you want?

106
00:10:10,792 --> 00:10:14,248
I'm Beowulf, and I need
some food and rest.

107
00:10:14,344 --> 00:10:16,264
He's one of them.

108
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:20,008
How else could he have
gotten through?

109
00:10:20,104 --> 00:10:21,928
Go on back to your friends.

110
00:10:22,024 --> 00:10:25,576
- I'm not one of them.
- And you're not one of us.

111
00:10:25,672 --> 00:10:28,552
No, but by the looks of things,

112
00:10:28,648 --> 00:10:31,304
you would think an additional
sword would be welcome.

113
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:33,800
If he's good enough
to get through the siege scum,

114
00:10:33,992 --> 00:10:35,816
the border lord
should talk to him.

115
00:10:35,912 --> 00:10:37,832
We can always kill him later.

116
00:10:39,272 --> 00:10:41,864
It's for Hrothgarto decide.

117
00:10:44,168 --> 00:10:47,240
You may enter,
with no guarantee of safe passage.

118
00:10:47,336 --> 00:10:49,640
I'll take the chance.

119
00:10:54,344 --> 00:10:56,744
[ Whinnying ]

120
00:11:21,192 --> 00:11:24,264
[ Man On Loudspeaker, Indistinct ]

121
00:11:27,048 --> 00:11:28,872
Gates closed.

122
00:11:28,968 --> 00:11:31,080
Gates secured.

123
00:12:39,816 --> 00:12:41,640
Follow me.

124
00:12:53,832 --> 00:12:56,232
Beowulf. I've heard
that name before.

125
00:12:56,328 --> 00:12:59,016
- What'd you hear?
- Stories only idiots would believe.

126
00:12:59,112 --> 00:13:01,512
Only an idiot would come
to this damn place.

127
00:13:01,608 --> 00:13:05,064
Unless he was already damned.

128
00:13:18,376 --> 00:13:21,160
A mercenary.

129
00:13:21,256 --> 00:13:25,384
It's not something
we've come to expect around here.

130
00:13:26,920 --> 00:13:29,032
How did you get through
the siege lines?

131
00:13:29,128 --> 00:13:31,432
On my horse.

132
00:13:33,640 --> 00:13:35,944
You just asked them nicely?

133
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:38,632
Something like that.

134
00:13:38,728 --> 00:13:41,864
You think that we've
got buried gold here?

135
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:45,032
Or are you just a lover
Of drafty, old outposts?

136
00:13:45,128 --> 00:13:46,952
Neither.

137
00:13:48,584 --> 00:13:50,888
Then what brings you?

138
00:13:50,984 --> 00:13:52,808
The darkness.

139
00:13:56,168 --> 00:13:58,856
You know about...

140
00:13:58,952 --> 00:14:00,776
our problem?

141
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:05,096
And what?

142
00:14:05,192 --> 00:14:08,264
You're offering to help?

143
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:10,184
Yes.

144
00:14:16,872 --> 00:14:19,656
No sane man would come here
to face this thing.

145
00:14:19,752 --> 00:14:23,784
- I have no choice.
- You make it sound personal.

146
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:26,952
Border Lord, we don't know anything
about this man. Send him back.

147
00:14:27,048 --> 00:14:31,560
Roland, we have less
than 40 men left.

148
00:14:31,656 --> 00:14:35,112
And, as you noted,
night comes quickly.

149
00:14:37,512 --> 00:14:40,104
Give him Nivri's room.

150
00:14:44,328 --> 00:14:46,408
Will!

151
00:14:51,304 --> 00:14:53,128
Nivri's room.

152
00:15:02,536 --> 00:15:04,648
[Roland]
He's dangerous.

153
00:15:04,744 --> 00:15:06,568
Definitely.

154
00:15:06,664 --> 00:15:09,640
Until now, at least, we could
trust our guys on the inside.

155
00:15:09,736 --> 00:15:13,000
He's not from the siege lines.

156
00:15:13,096 --> 00:15:15,208
No man who's been
sitting out there...

157
00:15:15,304 --> 00:15:17,512
night after night,
knowing what's happening here,

158
00:15:17,608 --> 00:15:20,552
would willingly come to this place.

159
00:15:20,648 --> 00:15:22,760
There's something else.

160
00:15:22,856 --> 00:15:24,584
He may have been sent
by Nivri's family.

161
00:15:26,120 --> 00:15:28,232
Revenge for
your son-in-law's death.

162
00:15:28,328 --> 00:15:30,344
They lost their only son.

163
00:15:32,072 --> 00:15:35,048
If they believe his death
was no accident,

164
00:15:35,144 --> 00:15:36,968
they would want retaliation.

165
00:15:37,064 --> 00:15:41,096
Who ever he is, let's see
How he feels in the morning.

166
00:15:42,920 --> 00:15:46,472
He'll either be out of here or
getting a look at our crematorium.

167
00:15:48,104 --> 00:15:49,896
Either way,

168
00:15:49,992 --> 00:15:51,816
problem solved.

169
00:15:57,192 --> 00:15:59,592
And the weapons master,
that's my uncle.

170
00:15:59,688 --> 00:16:02,280
That's why I am
the assistant weapons master.

171
00:16:02,376 --> 00:16:04,200
Not because I'm any good at it.

172
00:16:04,296 --> 00:16:06,792
Once I get outta here,
I'm heading east towards the water.

173
00:16:06,888 --> 00:16:09,768
- You think you'll get out?
- You see that girl Pendra?

174
00:16:09,864 --> 00:16:11,688
She and I were supposed
to go together,

175
00:16:11,784 --> 00:16:14,376
and as you can see,
things didn't work out so good.

176
00:16:14,472 --> 00:16:17,448
So I'm still here.
Why, do you think we'll get out?

177
00:16:17,544 --> 00:16:19,368
Probably not.

178
00:16:24,424 --> 00:16:26,440
Well, this is it.

179
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:30,472
Who is Nivri?

180
00:16:30,568 --> 00:16:33,736
Nivri was the border lord's
son-in-law. He was married to Kyra.

181
00:16:33,832 --> 00:16:36,520
- "Was"?
- Yeah. Killed.

182
00:16:41,992 --> 00:16:43,816
What's this?

183
00:16:43,912 --> 00:16:45,928
I wouldn't touch that.
The beast got him?

184
00:16:46,024 --> 00:16:48,424
Oh, no, no.
Before the beast.

185
00:16:50,824 --> 00:16:54,248
- [ Panting ]
- Assistant weapons master?

186
00:16:54,344 --> 00:16:57,608
Yeah. Ironic, huh?

187
00:16:59,336 --> 00:17:01,160
How did he die?

188
00:17:01,256 --> 00:17:03,080
Well, he--

189
00:17:15,944 --> 00:17:17,768
A guest.

190
00:17:17,864 --> 00:17:19,688
How unlikely.

191
00:17:23,624 --> 00:17:26,472
My husband used to come here
when he drank.

192
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:30,504
I haven't been here
since he died.

193
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:32,424
My condolences.

194
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:35,304
I know the reason you're here.

195
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:37,608
His family sentyou, didn't they?

196
00:17:37,704 --> 00:17:39,528
Nobody sent me.

197
00:17:40,968 --> 00:17:43,368
What do they want from us?

198
00:17:43,464 --> 00:17:46,728
Titles?
His share of the land?

199
00:17:46,824 --> 00:17:48,648
Will that satisfy them?

200
00:17:48,744 --> 00:17:51,144
I'm not who you think I am.

201
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:53,640
His death was an accident.

202
00:17:53,736 --> 00:17:56,232
At weapons practice with Roland.

203
00:17:56,328 --> 00:18:00,040
Weapons practice
can be so dangerous.

204
00:18:03,592 --> 00:18:06,376
You claim to be here
to fight our beast.

205
00:18:06,472 --> 00:18:09,544
It's not a claim.
It's the truth.

206
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:12,712
Well, it can't be killed.

207
00:18:12,808 --> 00:18:15,592
Not by my father, or Roland,

208
00:18:15,688 --> 00:18:17,512
or any man.

209
00:18:17,608 --> 00:18:20,488
I'm not like other men.

210
00:18:22,312 --> 00:18:25,672
That... you will have to prove.

211
00:18:34,184 --> 00:18:37,256
What's going to happen
when the beast comes?

212
00:18:46,856 --> 00:18:49,256
[ Exhales ]

213
00:18:50,696 --> 00:18:53,768
Doesn't matter if you're tired.

214
00:18:53,864 --> 00:18:56,456
You can sleep when you're dead.

215
00:18:56,552 --> 00:18:59,624
Get up!
Come on, it's a practice!

216
00:18:59,720 --> 00:19:03,816
Surround me. Come on,
surround me! Come on! Boo!

217
00:19:03,912 --> 00:19:06,120
My goodness.

218
00:19:06,216 --> 00:19:08,040
Come on!

219
00:19:08,136 --> 00:19:11,784
Why does he keep driving 'em on
when they're too tired to stand up?

220
00:19:11,880 --> 00:19:13,704
- Move!
- He's a machine.

221
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:16,680
Suppose there's no point in telling
Roland they'll be dead tomorrow.

222
00:19:17,928 --> 00:19:21,480
You attack me.
You understand? You attack me!

223
00:19:21,576 --> 00:19:23,688
And always remember:

224
00:19:25,224 --> 00:19:29,352
It's not about weapons.
In here it counts.

225
00:19:35,752 --> 00:19:38,152
It's not over yet.
Come on! Come on!

226
00:19:38,248 --> 00:19:40,552
- Come on!
- [ Grunts ]

227
00:19:47,752 --> 00:19:49,960
Attack me.

228
00:19:54,280 --> 00:19:56,008
Come on.

229
00:20:01,288 --> 00:20:04,072
Now you, take my sword.

230
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:07,880
Aaah!

231
00:20:18,824 --> 00:20:21,032
Fight well...

232
00:20:22,088 --> 00:20:24,008
or die badly.

233
00:20:29,768 --> 00:20:31,592
Sir.

234
00:20:38,952 --> 00:20:41,736
I wonder how many
will die tonight.

235
00:21:13,768 --> 00:21:16,744
[Door Creaks Open]

236
00:21:17,992 --> 00:21:19,816
Didn't mean to scare you.

237
00:21:20,008 --> 00:21:22,024
Permanent state around here.

238
00:21:22,120 --> 00:21:25,768
My useless nephew, where did
you put the replacement bolts?

239
00:21:25,864 --> 00:21:28,168
Huh? Huh?

240
00:21:28,264 --> 00:21:31,432
Just once it would be good if he put
something where it's supposed to be.

241
00:21:31,528 --> 00:21:34,408
He's a good kid.
Give him a chance. He'll be fine.

242
00:21:34,504 --> 00:21:37,864
Yeah, if he don't
get us all killed first.

243
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:41,576
- You all right out there?
- Oh, yeah.

244
00:21:41,672 --> 00:21:43,880
I'll have some of that later.

245
00:21:47,336 --> 00:21:49,352
[Door Creaking, Closing]

246
00:21:58,088 --> 00:22:01,160
I must apologize
for the quality of the food.

247
00:22:01,256 --> 00:22:04,712
We did stock pile supplies
in case of such an emergency,

248
00:22:04,808 --> 00:22:07,688
and so provisions
were not initially a problem.

249
00:22:07,784 --> 00:22:10,952
But now, nothing getting in,
nothing getting out.

250
00:22:11,048 --> 00:22:14,088
And when the storeroom was full,
It didn't contain a single thing...

251
00:22:14,184 --> 00:22:16,200
that was of any interest
to our intruder,

252
00:22:16,296 --> 00:22:19,272
who seems to prefer... us.

253
00:22:19,368 --> 00:22:21,192
This is my daughter, Kyra.

254
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:25,704
We've already met.

255
00:22:28,104 --> 00:22:31,656
Will your wife be joining us?

256
00:22:31,752 --> 00:22:34,056
My wife died many years ago.

257
00:22:36,264 --> 00:22:38,952
It was a tragic accident.

258
00:22:39,048 --> 00:22:41,448
She was new to the outpost,

259
00:22:41,544 --> 00:22:43,944
walking alone at night.

260
00:22:44,040 --> 00:22:45,832
She fell from the battlements.

261
00:22:47,848 --> 00:22:50,152
Do you have family, Beowulf?

262
00:22:50,248 --> 00:22:53,032
I've never wanted a family.

263
00:22:53,224 --> 00:22:57,256
I thought it only natural
to desire home, family.

264
00:22:57,352 --> 00:23:00,808
Then I have no natural desires.

265
00:23:00,904 --> 00:23:04,456
Interesting.
How so?

266
00:23:04,552 --> 00:23:08,488
Since I have no desire to stay in
One place, a home would be useless.

267
00:23:08,584 --> 00:23:10,984
And I have no desire for a family...

268
00:23:11,080 --> 00:23:13,384
since I don't want to
create more like me.

269
00:23:13,480 --> 00:23:16,840
So that your ego
can rest assured of your uniqueness.

270
00:23:18,920 --> 00:23:21,320
Exactly.

271
00:23:27,752 --> 00:23:31,208
You must excuse my daughter.

272
00:23:31,304 --> 00:23:34,184
She's always been a woman
of her own mind.

273
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:37,064
And my father has always been
an expert at making my excuses.

274
00:24:15,336 --> 00:24:17,160
- Damn!
- [Clattering]

275
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:28,840
[Quiet Rustling Sound]

276
00:24:28,936 --> 00:24:30,760
Oh, uh, Karl?

277
00:24:30,856 --> 00:24:34,600
I dropped my glasses somewhere.
You see 'em anywhere?

278
00:24:37,192 --> 00:24:39,016
Karl?

279
00:24:40,744 --> 00:24:43,720
Is that you, Karl?

280
00:24:46,504 --> 00:24:49,576
If there was a high point,
it was the Underlands' siege.

281
00:24:49,672 --> 00:24:51,592
I remember.

282
00:24:51,688 --> 00:24:55,688
It was an active year. We were
fighting under great pressure.

283
00:24:57,128 --> 00:24:59,528
But we were strong...

284
00:24:59,720 --> 00:25:03,272
'cause the fighters
worked together as a unit.

285
00:25:03,368 --> 00:25:06,152
I don't think after those advances,
we should--

286
00:25:06,248 --> 00:25:08,744
- Is something wrong?
- Can you sense it?

287
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:12,104
Sense what?

288
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:14,312
This is bullshit!

289
00:25:14,408 --> 00:25:16,712
What is it?

290
00:25:16,808 --> 00:25:19,784
Evil. It's here.

291
00:25:23,432 --> 00:25:25,800
Hrothgar,
this is ridiculous.

292
00:25:25,896 --> 00:25:27,720
We need fighting men,
not lunatics.

293
00:25:27,912 --> 00:25:29,832
- Roland, be quiet.
- What, me?

294
00:25:32,040 --> 00:25:34,632
The weapons master,
he's dead.

295
00:25:53,544 --> 00:25:55,752
It's changing its method.

296
00:25:55,848 --> 00:25:59,272
- Never killed so early before.
- It knows.

297
00:26:16,072 --> 00:26:18,568
I'm sorry, Will.

298
00:26:18,664 --> 00:26:21,256
You're the weapons
master now.

299
00:26:27,688 --> 00:26:29,960
[ Sighs ]

300
00:26:34,088 --> 00:26:36,296
Promotion.

301
00:26:36,392 --> 00:26:38,504
Yeah, not too comforting, huh?

302
00:26:38,600 --> 00:26:42,344
You could say that. Of course,
everyone's gonna die anyway,

303
00:26:42,440 --> 00:26:44,744
but one thing's for sure is
I ain't no weapons master.

304
00:26:44,840 --> 00:26:47,912
You don't have to be good
all the time,

305
00:26:48,008 --> 00:26:50,696
just when it matters.

306
00:27:27,816 --> 00:27:31,752
You're not really here because
of my husband's death, are you?

307
00:27:34,408 --> 00:27:37,000
No.

308
00:27:37,096 --> 00:27:39,784
But if I was,
I would be after Roland,

309
00:27:39,880 --> 00:27:42,088
so why would you be afraid?

310
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:45,544
I'm not afraid.

311
00:27:46,696 --> 00:27:49,288
I can't afford to be afraid.

312
00:27:50,632 --> 00:27:52,552
Don't you have any fear?

313
00:27:52,648 --> 00:27:55,624
Fear is all I know.

314
00:27:55,720 --> 00:27:57,352
You can feel it.

315
00:27:59,560 --> 00:28:01,384
You can sense it.

316
00:28:02,728 --> 00:28:04,744
Yes.

317
00:28:04,840 --> 00:28:06,632
You said it knows.

318
00:28:07,688 --> 00:28:09,512
What did you mean?

319
00:28:11,336 --> 00:28:13,832
It knows I'm here.

320
00:28:18,248 --> 00:28:20,072
What are you?

321
00:28:20,168 --> 00:28:23,240
I'm trapped between two worlds.

322
00:28:23,336 --> 00:28:25,736
That's what I am.

323
00:28:40,968 --> 00:28:42,600
You can't have her.

324
00:28:42,792 --> 00:28:45,480
I'm not in your way.

325
00:28:45,576 --> 00:28:47,400
I think you are.

326
00:28:47,496 --> 00:28:50,376
You manipulate her
and Hrothgar, but not me.

327
00:28:53,064 --> 00:28:55,944
- We need each other.
- I need no one.

328
00:28:56,040 --> 00:28:57,864
You better go.

329
00:28:58,920 --> 00:29:01,704
- I have to stay.
- Then you fight.

330
00:29:17,608 --> 00:29:19,624
Yaah! Aah!

331
00:29:32,680 --> 00:29:34,888
Aaah!

332
00:29:41,384 --> 00:29:44,168
Don't push your luck, Roland.

333
00:29:45,608 --> 00:29:47,528
Stay sharp.

334
00:30:43,272 --> 00:30:46,120
I'm here to sweeten
your dreams, my love.

335
00:30:51,496 --> 00:30:53,320
[ Moans ]

336
00:31:04,936 --> 00:31:08,680
[ Panting ]

337
00:31:29,576 --> 00:31:31,880
It's almost finished, my love.

338
00:31:33,512 --> 00:31:36,296
- It's almost finished, my love.
- [ Gasps ]

339
00:31:36,392 --> 00:31:39,752
[ Panting ]

340
00:31:50,472 --> 00:31:52,392
[Quiet Growl]

341
00:31:52,488 --> 00:31:54,984
[ Panting ]

342
00:32:31,144 --> 00:32:33,448
[Metal Creaking]

343
00:32:35,560 --> 00:32:37,384
[Creaking Continues]

344
00:32:45,448 --> 00:32:47,272
[Door Squeaking]

345
00:33:01,640 --> 00:33:04,328
[ Gasps ]
Goddamn!

346
00:33:04,424 --> 00:33:06,248
Geez, Karl.
Get a grip, man.

347
00:33:06,344 --> 00:33:08,840
Sorry. I thought
I heard something.

348
00:33:08,936 --> 00:33:12,200
Yeah?
You heard me!

349
00:33:12,296 --> 00:33:16,328
You know, Karl, with all the real
cool ways to die around here,

350
00:33:16,424 --> 00:33:18,728
I'd rather not go by heart attack.

351
00:33:20,072 --> 00:33:22,952
[Will]
Uh, let's see.

352
00:33:23,048 --> 00:33:24,840
Look at all this.

353
00:33:24,936 --> 00:33:28,104
You'd think with all this stuff,
we'd be able to kick some ass.

354
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:30,600
How do you tell all the junk
from the critical stuff?

355
00:33:30,696 --> 00:33:32,904
Your uncle knew.

356
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:35,592
Yeah, well,
that's real helpful, Karl.

357
00:33:35,688 --> 00:33:38,184
Okay, come on. Let's go.
Let's go. Let's do something.

358
00:33:38,280 --> 00:33:40,104
I'll get the blasters.

359
00:33:40,200 --> 00:33:42,120
[ Sighs ]

360
00:34:02,536 --> 00:34:06,280
Karl, I think I broke it.
Can you come fix this damn thing?

361
00:34:06,376 --> 00:34:08,968
I'll get the blasters.

362
00:34:28,456 --> 00:34:30,728
[Machinery Whirring]

363
00:34:38,216 --> 00:34:40,424
[Metal Clanging]

364
00:34:40,520 --> 00:34:43,304
Will? You okay?

365
00:34:48,392 --> 00:34:51,368
[Clattering]

366
00:35:14,952 --> 00:35:18,504
[ Growling ]

367
00:35:25,416 --> 00:35:30,024
[ Sniffs, Coughing ]
Oh, man, I saw it.

368
00:35:30,120 --> 00:35:33,160
- [Coughs]
- How big was it?

369
00:35:33,256 --> 00:35:35,656
What kind of armor?

370
00:35:35,752 --> 00:35:38,344
Was it shielded?
Was it exposed?

371
00:35:38,440 --> 00:35:42,280
It was--
Man, it was ugly.

372
00:35:48,808 --> 00:35:51,784
It came in broad daylight.

373
00:35:51,880 --> 00:35:55,912
It's tiring of the game.
It wants it done.

374
00:35:59,368 --> 00:36:01,768
Put the women and children
into the sanctuary.

375
00:36:01,864 --> 00:36:05,576
Everyone else patrols in threes and
keep visual contact at all times.

376
00:36:05,672 --> 00:36:07,496
Kyra.

377
00:36:09,128 --> 00:36:11,336
I won't be herded
and locked away.

378
00:36:11,432 --> 00:36:15,560
- I'm fighting this time.
-Join the others in the sanctuary.

379
00:36:15,656 --> 00:36:19,496
A little late to start
protecting me, isn't it, Father?

380
00:36:47,016 --> 00:36:49,800
[ Nervous Chattering ]

381
00:36:53,448 --> 00:36:57,000
- [Man]Hurry up. Hurry up.
- Hurry up.

382
00:37:08,488 --> 00:37:10,312
Where's Kyra?
Where is she?

383
00:37:10,408 --> 00:37:13,672
I don't know where she is.
I haven't seen her.

384
00:37:13,768 --> 00:37:16,072
[Woman]
We'll never get out of this.

385
00:37:18,856 --> 00:37:21,160
- Move in now.
- Make sure both doors are bolted.

386
00:37:21,256 --> 00:37:23,080
Yes, sir.

387
00:37:36,616 --> 00:37:38,440
All sanctuary doors secured.

388
00:37:40,712 --> 00:37:43,688
All sanctuary doors secured.

389
00:37:54,536 --> 00:37:57,512
- What is it?
- Is there any other way in?

390
00:37:57,608 --> 00:38:00,680
All doors are secured
from the inside.

391
00:38:02,408 --> 00:38:04,808
- [Beast Roaring]
- [People Screaming]

392
00:38:05,864 --> 00:38:08,936
[Roaring, Screaming Continue]

393
00:38:13,896 --> 00:38:17,064
[Screaming]

394
00:38:35,016 --> 00:38:38,760
[Child Crying]

395
00:40:27,400 --> 00:40:29,032
Aaaah!

396
00:40:58,472 --> 00:41:00,296
[Growls]

397
00:41:10,088 --> 00:41:12,200
- [ Growling ]
- Aaah!

398
00:41:28,200 --> 00:41:30,024
Aaah!

399
00:41:57,832 --> 00:42:00,328
[ Growls ]

400
00:42:25,768 --> 00:42:29,000
[Sword Hits Ground]

401
00:42:31,688 --> 00:42:34,472
Aaah!

402
00:42:36,392 --> 00:42:37,832
[ Groans ]

403
00:42:55,112 --> 00:42:57,896
[ Growling ]

404
00:43:02,088 --> 00:43:05,352
[ Screams, Roars ]

405
00:43:10,728 --> 00:43:13,128
[ Roaring ]

406
00:43:17,448 --> 00:43:18,984
Aaah! Daah!

407
00:43:25,224 --> 00:43:28,680
Me! Fight me!

408
00:43:28,776 --> 00:43:31,656
- [ Moans ]
- [ Beast Growls ]

409
00:43:31,752 --> 00:43:34,600
[ Growling ]
Not you.

410
00:43:44,200 --> 00:43:47,272
[ Exhales ]

411
00:43:50,632 --> 00:43:52,648
Please.

412
00:43:52,744 --> 00:43:54,568
[ Groans ]

413
00:43:55,816 --> 00:43:57,640
I can't--

414
00:44:06,248 --> 00:44:08,072
Damn.

415
00:44:27,272 --> 00:44:29,768
[Crematorium Door Closes]

416
00:45:19,912 --> 00:45:22,024
How is he?

417
00:45:23,752 --> 00:45:25,576
Dying.

418
00:45:26,920 --> 00:45:28,744
He saved my life.

419
00:45:34,024 --> 00:45:36,232
I need more bandages.

420
00:45:36,328 --> 00:45:38,536
He wounded the beast.

421
00:45:41,576 --> 00:45:43,400
Yes.

422
00:45:50,120 --> 00:45:52,040
That gives us a chance.

423
00:45:53,576 --> 00:45:55,304
Perhaps.

424
00:46:01,544 --> 00:46:03,464
Kyra?

425
00:46:07,112 --> 00:46:09,704
All I've ever wanted was you.

426
00:46:15,144 --> 00:46:16,968
I know.

427
00:46:18,984 --> 00:46:20,808
I know.

428
00:46:47,656 --> 00:46:49,576
It won't be long now.

429
00:47:24,968 --> 00:47:26,984
Sweet dreams, my love.

430
00:48:14,184 --> 00:48:16,008
[ Moaning ]

431
00:48:28,840 --> 00:48:32,488
Feel it-- the life your husband
put in my belly.

432
00:48:32,584 --> 00:48:34,504
- [ Laughs ]
- [ Panting ]

433
00:48:38,632 --> 00:48:40,456
It's almost finished,
my love.

434
00:48:43,528 --> 00:48:45,544
It's almost finished,
my love.

435
00:48:45,640 --> 00:48:49,096
[ Gasps, Panting ]

436
00:49:07,880 --> 00:49:09,992
[Footsteps]

437
00:49:50,184 --> 00:49:52,392
Don't be afraid.

438
00:49:59,080 --> 00:50:00,904
You should be dead.

439
00:50:01,000 --> 00:50:03,304
Many times.

440
00:50:03,400 --> 00:50:05,896
Explain.

441
00:50:05,992 --> 00:50:08,680
I'm a quick healer.

442
00:50:08,776 --> 00:50:12,520
- Not good enough.
- That's all I can say.

443
00:50:12,616 --> 00:50:15,688
Because you're afraid
the truth will send me running?

444
00:50:15,784 --> 00:50:18,856
From what
I've seen of you, no.

445
00:50:18,952 --> 00:50:21,064
But because there is no time.

446
00:50:24,712 --> 00:50:26,536
[Door Opens]

447
00:50:27,848 --> 00:50:30,632
[Beowulf]
Enjoying the view?

448
00:50:42,536 --> 00:50:44,936
A remarkable recovery.

449
00:50:45,992 --> 00:50:48,392
It wasn't as bad as it looked.

450
00:50:50,888 --> 00:50:53,960
We all have our secrets, I suppose.

451
00:50:55,400 --> 00:50:57,800
Tell me,

452
00:50:57,896 --> 00:51:01,416
if a man fights
a creature of evil,

453
00:51:03,144 --> 00:51:06,120
then he cannot be evil himself,

454
00:51:07,560 --> 00:51:09,768
can he?

455
00:51:09,864 --> 00:51:12,456
If you're looking for absolution,

456
00:51:12,552 --> 00:51:14,664
you're asking the wrong man.

457
00:51:19,656 --> 00:51:21,768
Whoever you are,

458
00:51:21,864 --> 00:51:24,648
whatever you are,

459
00:51:24,744 --> 00:51:27,048
I thank you for your help.

460
00:51:27,144 --> 00:51:30,312
Why...

461
00:51:30,408 --> 00:51:32,488
"not you"?

462
00:51:45,160 --> 00:51:47,752
[Foot steps Approaching]

463
00:51:53,704 --> 00:51:57,640
[ Gasps ]
You scared the hell out of me.

464
00:51:57,736 --> 00:52:02,056
I need you to make me something,
and I need it now.

465
00:52:03,944 --> 00:52:05,864
Yeah, what is it?

466
00:52:05,960 --> 00:52:09,608
I'll show you. But no mistakes.

467
00:52:12,584 --> 00:52:14,696
All right, no sweat.

468
00:52:14,792 --> 00:52:17,480
This is the time...

469
00:52:17,576 --> 00:52:19,400
it matters.

470
00:52:28,328 --> 00:52:30,152
How's your leg?

471
00:52:30,248 --> 00:52:33,704
My injuries don't heal
as well as yours.

472
00:52:33,800 --> 00:52:36,072
I'll be little help like this.

473
00:52:36,168 --> 00:52:38,952
One day you'll have to
teach me your trick.

474
00:52:41,064 --> 00:52:43,464
What can I do?

475
00:52:43,656 --> 00:52:47,112
Nothing.

476
00:52:47,208 --> 00:52:49,320
It'll be over tonight?

477
00:52:49,416 --> 00:52:51,528
Yes, one way or another.

478
00:52:51,624 --> 00:52:53,832
It's time.

479
00:52:53,928 --> 00:52:56,808
It will come for me,

480
00:52:56,904 --> 00:52:59,304
but I will know where
it's coming from and when.

481
00:53:08,584 --> 00:53:11,560
There's one thing
you should know about Nivri.

482
00:53:12,808 --> 00:53:16,456
His family is very wealthy,
very rich.

483
00:53:16,552 --> 00:53:20,488
The marriage was arranged
by Hrothgar, not Kyra's choice.

484
00:53:20,584 --> 00:53:23,272
He was a sadist and a pig.

485
00:53:23,368 --> 00:53:26,344
He treated her badly, very badly.

486
00:53:27,496 --> 00:53:29,608
- But you didn't kill him?
- No, but I tried.

487
00:53:29,704 --> 00:53:34,216
I challenged the bastard to a fight,
but Hrothgar made me back off.

488
00:53:38,248 --> 00:53:40,232
You know, don't you?

489
00:53:44,168 --> 00:53:48,872
She thinks of me... as a brother.

490
00:53:53,288 --> 00:53:56,072
That's all I could ever be.

491
00:53:59,144 --> 00:54:01,064
I've survived a lot of pain.

492
00:54:01,160 --> 00:54:05,000
- Warriors do.
- Yeah.

493
00:54:06,536 --> 00:54:09,320
But nothing...
to compare with that.

494
00:54:16,872 --> 00:54:20,232
End its miserable life...

495
00:54:20,328 --> 00:54:22,152
tonight.

496
00:54:31,176 --> 00:54:33,576
- Is it done?
- Yep.

497
00:54:40,488 --> 00:54:44,488
- Have you tested it?
- Yeah. It works fine. Works great.

498
00:54:44,584 --> 00:54:46,696
Most of the time.

499
00:54:46,792 --> 00:54:49,864
No, it's fine. It's fine.

500
00:54:49,960 --> 00:54:53,992
It's fine. Hey, listen. Are you
gonna take this beast thing or not?

501
00:54:54,088 --> 00:54:56,776
You don't want me
to ruin the surprise.

502
00:54:57,928 --> 00:54:59,752
[ Chuckles ]

503
00:54:59,848 --> 00:55:02,632
Waking up in the morning
is surprise enough.

504
00:55:02,728 --> 00:55:05,896
- [Door Opens]
- [ Scoffs ]

505
00:55:17,000 --> 00:55:18,824
Beowulf.

506
00:55:23,624 --> 00:55:25,640
Don't do this.

507
00:55:25,832 --> 00:55:28,904
We all do what we have to do.

508
00:55:29,000 --> 00:55:31,400
You know that well, I think.

509
00:55:33,224 --> 00:55:35,720
Is that the knife
you used on your husband?

510
00:55:43,112 --> 00:55:45,800
What are you?

511
00:55:49,800 --> 00:55:52,968
Secrets are hard to keep.

512
00:55:55,848 --> 00:55:57,768
It was night.

513
00:55:59,688 --> 00:56:01,992
He'd been drinking as usual.

514
00:56:03,912 --> 00:56:06,120
He wanted me.

515
00:56:08,136 --> 00:56:10,248
I refused.

516
00:56:12,168 --> 00:56:14,568
He started to beat me.

517
00:56:17,832 --> 00:56:19,912
So I stabbed him...

518
00:56:21,256 --> 00:56:23,944
over...

519
00:56:24,136 --> 00:56:26,248
and over.

520
00:56:28,744 --> 00:56:31,240
And the whole time...

521
00:56:31,336 --> 00:56:34,696
he just stood there...

522
00:56:34,792 --> 00:56:37,192
looking surprised.

523
00:56:42,472 --> 00:56:45,640
Now he's come back to kill us,

524
00:56:45,736 --> 00:56:47,944
one by one,

525
00:56:50,056 --> 00:56:52,712
saving me for the last.

526
00:56:52,808 --> 00:56:55,784
The beast is not your husband.

527
00:56:55,880 --> 00:56:58,472
What makes you so sure?

528
00:56:58,664 --> 00:57:01,544
Ghosts don't eat people.

529
00:57:01,640 --> 00:57:03,560
This is not your doing.

530
00:57:03,752 --> 00:57:06,056
If someone is to blame,
it's not you.

531
00:57:06,152 --> 00:57:09,128
Maybe not for the first strike,

532
00:57:09,224 --> 00:57:11,528
but for the second...

533
00:57:11,624 --> 00:57:14,792
and the third and the fourth.

534
00:57:14,888 --> 00:57:17,672
- It was justified.
- It was murder.

535
00:57:17,768 --> 00:57:20,552
Yes.

